-- Amplats CEO says will not negotiate with illegal strikers
-- 
-- Wed Sep 26, 2012 9:18am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/09/26/us-safrica-mines-amplats-idUSBRE88P0W120120926

 

 JOHANNESBURG  (Reuters) - World No. 1 platinum producer Anglo American Platinum ( AMSJ.J ) will not negotiate on wage demands being made by illegal strikers at its key Rustenburg operations, its chief executive said on Wednesday. 
 Chris Griffith was speaking on a conference call after the company said it would take action which could include dismissals against workers who did not return to the shafts by Thursday. The company has lost 20,000 ounces in the stoppages since Sept 12. (Reporting by  Ed Stoddard  and Sherilee Lakmidas; Editing by  Pascal Fletcher )